---
import IdeasSidebar from "../../components/IdeasSidebar.astro";
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>mospresent — Present like you're broadcasting from the future</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="mospresent is a macOS virtual camera that blends your webcam with transparent slide content from Google Slides or PowerPoint, driven by hand gestures, speech, and optional LLM overlays."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/hub-subproject.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="hub-subproject">
    <IdeasSidebar active="mospresent" />

    <div class="hub-main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hub-status-row">
          <span class="hub-chip draft">🧊 Draft — concept only</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">mosaigo distribution</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">macOS virtual camera</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">gesture + voice driven</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Your slides, your face, <span class="accent">one stream</span>.</h1>
        <p class="tagline">mospresent is a macOS virtual camera that blends your webcam with transparent slide content from Google Slides or PowerPoint — driven by hand gestures, speech, and an optional local LLM. Present in Meet, Zoom, and Teams like you're broadcasting from the future.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="intent-callout">
          <h3>Intent</h3>
          <p><strong>In remote meetings, presence beats slides.</strong> Screen-share kills the presenter. Lightboards are beautiful but impractical. mospresent is the software version of a lightboard — your existing deck floats around you, your gestures drive it, your voice cues it, and the output is a standard virtual camera any conferencing app can select. You stay visible. Your audience stays engaged.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">The idea in one picture</div>
        <h2>Vision + audio + language, composed live</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Multiple parallel pipelines. Heavy work stays off the critical path via last-value stores, so end-to-end latency stays under 80 ms.</p>
        <div class="pipe-diagram">Webcam ──┐
         ├─→ Segment → Compose → Virtual Camera → Zoom / Meet / Teams
Slides ──┤           ↑
         │     Gesture · Speech · LLM cues
         └─→ Render transparent layers</div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Design principles</div>
        <h2>Five things mospresent holds firm</h2>
        <div class="diff-grid">
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon primary">👤</div>
            <h3>Presence over slides</h3>
            <p>The presenter is the primary subject. Slides orbit. No more tiny webcam tile in the corner while the deck hogs the screen.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon accent">📹</div>
            <h3>Zero conferencing changes</h3>
            <p>Output as a standard virtual camera. Any tool that can pick a camera — Zoom, Meet, Teams, Slack, Discord — works immediately.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon success">⚡</div>
            <h3>Latency is non-negotiable</h3>
            <p>End-to-end capture → composite → vcam under 80 ms. Heavy work (LLM, STT) runs in parallel and publishes to last-value stores.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon light">🔒</div>
            <h3>Local-first speech and vision</h3>
            <p>Whisper runs on-device. LLM runs locally via llama.cpp (or is disabled). Cloud is opt-in for users who want it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon error">📄</div>
            <h3>Your deck, unchanged</h3>
            <p>mospresent reads your .pptx or Google Slides deck directly. You don't re-author your content or learn a new authoring tool.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon muted">🎯</div>
            <h3>Driven by gesture and voice</h3>
            <p>Raise a hand to advance. Point to highlight. Speak a cue. The presenter's body and voice become the slide remote.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Step library (target)</div>
        <h2>Every capability is a step</h2>
        <div class="pkg-grid">
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">deck.parse.gslides</div><div class="pkg-desc">Fetch Google Slides deck via API</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">deck.parse.pptx</div><div class="pkg-desc">Parse local .pptx into structured Deck</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">slide.render.transparent</div><div class="pkg-desc">Rasterize slide to RGBA transparent layer</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">bg.segment.vision.ios</div><div class="pkg-desc">Apple Vision Person Segmentation</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">hand.detect.mediapipe</div><div class="pkg-desc">21-point hand landmarks</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">gesture.classify</div><div class="pkg-desc">Map landmarks to named gestures</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">stt.whisper.local</div><div class="pkg-desc">Whisper.cpp local speech-to-text</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">intent.classify</div><div class="pkg-desc">Transcript → IntentEvent</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">llm.overlay.suggest</div><div class="pkg-desc">Background LLM-proposed callouts</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">scene.layout.engine</div><div class="pkg-desc">Presenter-left/right/behind/PiP</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">scene.compose</div><div class="pkg-desc">Composite webcam + matte + slide + overlays</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">vcam.publish.macos</div><div class="pkg-desc">CoreMediaIO DAL extension output</div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Latency budget</div>
        <h2>Why the critical path is &lt; 30 ms</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Heavy work never blocks composition. LLM, STT, intent, and slide rendering all run on parallel pipelines and publish to last-value stores — the composite pipeline reads the freshest value every tick.</p>
        <div class="eco-grid">
          <div class="eco-card">
            <div class="eco-badge primary">critical path</div>
            <h3>Capture → Composite → DAL</h3>
            <p>Webcam capture (~5 ms) + composite with cached matte/slide/overlays (~15 ms) + DAL publish (~5 ms) = &lt; 30 ms. This runs every frame, no exceptions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="eco-card">
            <div class="eco-badge accent">parallel</div>
            <h3>Segmentation, STT, Gesture</h3>
            <p>Heavier per-frame work runs at its natural cadence on its own pipeline and publishes to last-value stores. The composite reads whatever's newest.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="eco-card">
            <div class="eco-badge success">background</div>
            <h3>LLM overlay suggestion</h3>
            <p>Runs at ~1 Hz. Takes the transcript window and current slide, asks a local model for a contextual callout, writes to last-value. Composite picks it up on the next frame.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-centered">
        <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
        <h2>One virtual camera, many parallel pipelines</h2>
        <div class="arch-visual">
          <div class="arch-layer accent">
            mospresent <span class="desc">Deck ingest · segmentation · gesture · speech · LLM · compose · vcam</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">imports &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer primary">
            mosoptics <span class="desc">Webcam capture · pose · hand detect · background segment</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer deep">
            mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine · topics · last-value stores · Studio</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="arch-caption">The macOS CMIO DAL plugin is the only native component. Everything else is Go pipelines.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
        <h2>From recorded clip to signed DAL plugin</h2>
        <div class="principle-grid">
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">01</div><div><h4>Composition loop on pre-rendered slides</h4><p>Webcam + segmentation + hard-coded layout → MP4 file. Prove the idea works end-to-end.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">02</div><div><h4>Virtual camera via NDI bridge</h4><p>mospresent appears in Zoom / Meet / Teams as a selectable camera. Full latency instrumentation.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">03</div><div><h4>Deck ingest (pptx + gslides)</h4><p>Parse real decks. Render transparent slide layers. Manual navigation from Studio.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">04</div><div><h4>Gesture navigation</h4><p>Trained classifier for raise_hand / point / pinch / open_palm. Gesture Trainer panel in Studio.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">05</div><div><h4>Speech navigation + LLM overlays</h4><p>Whisper local, intent classifier, LLM overlay suggestions with accept/dismiss UX.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">06</div><div><h4>Signed DAL plugin + release</h4><p>First-class macOS system camera. Install script, signing, public alpha.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="/staging/">mosaigo</a>
          <a href="/staging/mosoptics/">mosoptics</a>
          <a href="/ideas/moshome/">moshome</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mosbot/">mosbot</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mosops/">mosops</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mostrade/">mostrade</a>
          <a href="/ideas/depict/">depict</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mosarch/">mosarch</a>
          <a href="/ideas/aossc/">aossc</a>
        </div>
        <p>Part of the <a href="/staging/">mosaigoio</a> family · 🧊 draft subproject</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
